{{question-answer|question=11. Evaluate <math> \displaystyle \frac{3}{2^{-3}} </math>|answer={{noprint|1= <math> 24 </math>}}}}
{{question-answer|question=12. Simplify <math> (-3ab^3)(a^{-1}b^{-1}) </math>|answer={{noprint|1= <math> -3b^2 </math>}}}}
{{question-answer|question=13. Simplify <math> \displaystyle \frac{10a^3b^{-2}}{5a^2b^{-3}} </math>|answer={{noprint|1= <math>  2ab</math>}}}}
{{question-answer|question=14. Simplify <math> 16a^3b^7(2a^{-1}b^2)^{-2} </math>|answer={{noprint|1= <math> 4a^5b^3 </math>}}}}
{{question-answer|question=15. Evaluate <math> 125^{2/3} </math>|answer={{noprint|1= <math> 25 </math>}}}}
{{question-answer|question=16. Evaluate <math> (27/8)^{-1/3} </math>|answer={{noprint|1= <math> 2/3 </math>}}}}
{{question-answer|question=17. Rationalize the denominator and simplify: <math> \displaystyle \frac{1 - 3\sqrt{2}}{\sqrt{2} + 4} </math>|answer={{noprint|1= <math> \displaystyle \frac{13\sqrt2 - 10}{14} </math>}}}}

== Polynomials ==

{{question-answer|question=30. Rewrite the expression <math>(x^2-1)(2x+3)</math> as a polynomial in the standard form and state the degree of the polynomial. |answer={{noprint|1= <math>2x^3 + 3x^2 - 2x - 3</math>, degree 3}}}}
{{question-answer|question=31. Rewrite the expression <math>5x^{17}(4x^{-3} - 2x^{-2})</math> as a polynomial in the standard form and state the degree of the polynomial. |answer={{noprint|1= <math> - 10x^{15} + 20x^{14}</math>, degree 15}}}}
{{question-answer|question=32. Rewrite the expression <math>6(y^3 - y)^2 - 2y^4(3y^2 - 6)</math> as a polynomial in the standard form and state the degree of the polynomial. |answer={{noprint|1= <math>6y^2</math>, degree 2}}}}
{{question-answer|question=33. Evaluate the polynomial expression <math>4x^2 + 3x - 2</math> at <math>x = -5</math>|answer={{noprint|1= <math>113</math>}}}}

== Factoring ==

We are only interested in factors that have integer coefficients.

{{question-answer|question=40. Factor <math>60x^2y + 20xy - 12xy^3</math>|answer={{noprint|1= <math>4xy(15x + 5 - 3y^2)</math>}}}}
{{question-answer|question=41. Factor <math>x^2 + x - 20</math>|answer={{noprint|1= <math>(x+5)(x-4)</math>}}}}
{{question-answer|question=42. Show that the polynomial <math>3x^2 + 5x + 3</math> is irreducible (that is, cannot be factored using real coefficients)|answer={{noprint|1= <math>b^2-4ac = 5^2 - 4\cdot3\cdot3 = -11 < 0</math>}}}}
{{question-answer|question=43. Factor <math>6x^2 - 5x - 4</math>|answer={{noprint|1= <math>(3x - 4)(2x + 1)</math>}}}}
{{question-answer|question=44. Factor <math>9x^6 - 16x^4</math>|answer={{noprint|1= <math>x^4(3x + 4)(3x - 4)</math>}}}}
{{question-answer|question=45. Factor <math>9x^2y^2 - 12xyz + 4z^2</math>|answer={{noprint|1= <math>(3xy - 2z)^2</math>}}}}
{{question-answer|question=46. Factor <math>-2z^3+z^2-6z+3</math>|answer={{noprint|1= <math>(z^2+3)(1-2z)</math>}}}}

== Linear Equations ==

{{question-answer|question=50. You want to install hardwood floor tile. The delivery fee is $80, and the installation costs $6 per square foot (parts and labor). How many square feet can you tile on a $1100 budget? |answer={{noprint|1= 170 square feet}}}}
{{question-answer|question=51. Your distant relative's will stipulates that her money is to be divided between you, your sibling, and your child in such a way that your sibling gets twice as much as you do, and your child gets half as much as you do. How much money will you get if the total inheritance is seven hundred thousand dollars? |answer={{noprint|1= $200000}}}}
{{question-answer|question=52. Solve the equation <math>3 - 2x = x + 9</math>.|answer={{noprint|1= <math>x = -2</math>}}}}
{{question-answer|question=53. Solve the equation <math>2(x + 7) = -3(x + 1 - 2(x - 1))</math>.|answer={{noprint|1= <math>x = 23</math>}}}}
{{question-answer|question=54. Determine whether the equation <math>2(x - 1) = -2(1 - x)</math> is conditional, a contradiction, or an identity.|answer={{noprint|1= Identity}}}}
{{question-answer|question=55. Solve the equation <math>\displaystyle\left|\frac{4-x}{2}\right| = 3</math>.|answer={{noprint|1= <math>\{-2, 10\}</math>}}}}
{{question-answer|question=56. Solve the equation <math>|1 - 2(3 - x)| = 15</math>.|answer={{noprint|1= <math>\{-5, 10\}</math>}}}}

== Formulas ==
{{question-answer|question=60. Solve the formula <math>E = mc^2</math> for <math>m</math> ([[w:Mass-energy equivalence|Mass-energy equivalence]]). |answer={{noprint|1= <math>m = Ec^{-2}</math>}}}}
{{question-answer|question=61. Solve the formula <math>\displaystyle C = \frac59(F - 32)</math> for <math>F</math> ([[w:Fahrenheit#Definition_and_conversions|Fahrenheit to Celsius conversion]]).|answer={{noprint|1= <math>F = \frac95C+32</math>}}}}

