{{question-answer|question=202. Rewrite the expression <math>\displaystyle \frac12\log_3(x) - \log_3(y^2) + 2\log_3(x+2)</math> as a single logarithm with coefficient <math>1</math>.|answer={{noprint|1= <math>\displaystyle \log_3\left(\frac{(x+2)^2\sqrt x}{y}\right)</math>}}}}

