== Differentiation Review ==

{{question-answer|question=1. Write the product function <math>f(x)</math> and its rate of change function for <math>g(x) = 2e^5x</math> and <math>h(x) = 2x^2 - x</math>. |answer={{noprint|1= <math>f(x) = 2e^5x(2x^2 - x),\ f'(x) = 2e^5(2x^2 - x) + 2e^5x(4x - 1)</math>}}}}
{{question-answer|question=2. Write the product function <math>f(x)</math> and its rate of change function for <math>g(x) = 0.5\cos(4x)</math> and <math>h(x) = 2\ln(x)</math>. |answer={{noprint|1= <math>f(x) = \cos(4x)\ln(x),\ f'(x) = -4\sin(4x)\ln(x) + \frac{\cos(4x)}x</math>}}}}
{{question-answer|question=3. Find <math>f'(x)</math> if <math>f(x) = (2x+3)e^{-x}</math>. |answer={{noprint|1= <math>2e^{-x}-(2x+3)e^{-x}</math>}}}}
{{question-answer|question=4. Find <math>f'(x)</math> if <math>f(x) = 2\sqrt{x^3}\ln(x)</math>. |answer={{noprint|1= <math>3\sqrt{x}\ln(x) + 2\sqrt{x}</math>}}}}
