{{status|0%}}{{DISPLAYTITLE:Abstract Data Structures}}
<!-- A data type is a set of values and the basic operations that can be applied to values of that type. An abstract data type, therefore, is a data type whose properties (data and operations) are specified independently of any particular implementation. Remember that the goal in design is to reduce complexity through abstraction. If one can define useful struyctures and the operations that manipulate them at the logical level, one can use them as if they exist when needed in their designs. -->

